cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image processing and computer vision tasks such as shadow removal, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel network structure for shadow removal, which involves multi-context features for attention and prediction, indicating the use of deep learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of the current datasets and proposes a shadow matting generative adversarial network to synthesize realistic shadow mattings, which involves image synthesis techniques (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of limited datasets and the need for enhancing the textural understanding of the network, which indicates the use of artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents experimental results and discusses the quality of the produced images, indicating the use of multimedia techniques (cs.MM).
